title: For Sale/Trade:  Steyr M40
postcontent:
I am slowly getting out of the ".40 game" and this is one of the pistols I am looking to trade. It's a Steyr M40. Not a super rare gun but not all that common either; I have only seen a handful of these. I have always thought very highly of Steyr; they are some great quality firearms. It handles very well and is a very innovative handgun, including features such as an exceptionally low bore axis, trapazoid sights and finger-tip safety. The trigger is incredibly smooth, something like 5.5lbs, as close to a 1911 trigger as any polymer pistol will get. It is a very solid gun and well engineered. The M40 was designed from the ground-up as a .40 handgun, the story goes that the designer, Wilhelm Bubits, originally worked for Glock and that this (the M40) was his view of the next generation of polymer pistols.

It has some honest holster wear, and is 100% reliable. I am the second owner and have put in the neighborhood of 500rds through it with zero malfunctions. Included is the original case with booklets and integrated key, plus two 10rd mags and two ban-era 12rd mags (not included if MA buyer).

I am looking to trade for a Glock 17 + cash (preferably a 2nd gen). I am open to other trades and cash offers. Extra's such as night sights and pre-ban mags will be taken into consideration. I'd prefer an FTF in NH (buyer must hold P&R and agree to a bill of sale), but would be willing to do an FFL transfer to a MA resident.

This Walther bears little resemblance to the legendary PP and PPK pistols. It is also well away from the size and weight ranges seen in the other eight guns. This made the shooting exercises a good bit easier than with the other guns, although there were still a few malfunctions. We used the single-action aspect of the trigger system. The generous butt section and large adjustable sights made it even easier. This design actually began with the company’s inexpensive rimfire pistol, which has the same receiver shell. They put a different slide on top and added proper sights to produce a nice, medium-size .380 pistol. With modernistic styling, the PK380 is rakish-looking, and that alone will sell some guns. Don’t be confused by the Walther-like lever on the rear of the slide. It is nothing more than a safety block that pivots into the path of the hammer, preventing a strike on the firing pin. It is not the decocker mechanism we are used to seeing on Walthers

"I still have the gun..Its in a perfect condition,comes with all papers including purchase manuals,insurance,tools,Original box,all paper works Cleaning Brush and other accessories.It has no scratches or handling mark because i didn't really use it....It has a good feel in the hand and also has a good balance....I am selling this lovely gun because i'm in a huge Money problem and have no choice than to put a few  things out for
quick sale,that is why i am really looking out for cash only,not interested in trades..I am currently in Illinois...I listed the gun here because I bought it here and also feel i would get a quick and serious buyer from here( I deeply apologize for the little mix up
regarding the location).I can deactivate the  listing ,so that you can consider the sold to you .I'm available for a FTF here in Illinois or better still i will handle shipping cost/expenses to your FFL dealer.I'm a military man so shipping is no problem,telling you this so that you can know the kind of person you are dealing with... Let me know what works for you.... Thanks Kindly send payment  and FFL to :
Toshia Tapia
7502 Washington St, Hanover Park, IL 60133
Once payment is in the mail,get back at me with payment receipt and
tracking# and once i get payment,I will ship out the gun that same day
via UPS next day delivery..Do we have a deal?
Toshia"

After doing some research I found the mugshot and other evidence of "Toshia Tapia" trying to pull the same scam on other sites like AR-15.com, so as a reminder anyone who asks you to send a money order, cashier's check or payment in advance is probably out to scam you!
